> Looking for a quick "all-in-one" Thanksgiving dinner? Try this delicious meal that
> hits every holiday note. Center stage are juicy turkey cutlets drizzled with
> velvety homestyle garlic and sage gravy. On the side are roasted Brussels
> sprouts and smooth, buttery mashed sweet potatoes topped with candied pecans
> to complete this festive feast.

== Mashed Sweet Potatoes ==

Arrange rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Peel and dice @Sweet Potatoes{2} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by
2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup sweet potato cooking liquid, then drain and return sweet potatoes
to pot. Cover to keep warm until ready to mash in Step 5.

== Brussels Sprouts ==

While sweet potatoes cook, trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} (quarter any
larger sprouts). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{3%clove}. Pick @Sage{¼%ounce}
leaves from stems and mince.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{},
and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

> Tent sprouts with foil to keep warm until ready to serve.

== Candied Pecans ==

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @water{2%tablespoon},
@Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon}, @Cinnamon{¼%tsp}, and a pinch of salt
(@Salt{}); whisk to combine.

Stir in @Pecans{1%ounce} and cook, stirring constantly, until pecans are fragrant
and glazed, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

== Turkey ==

Pat @Turkey Breast Cutlet{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with
@Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for pecans over medium-high heat. Add
turkey and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-8%minutes} per side.

> Tip: Cook in batches if necessary; reduce heat and cover pan if turkey begins
> to brown too quickly.

Transfer turkey to a #cutting board{}.

== Mashed Sweet Potatoes - Finish ==

Mash sweet potatoes with @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon}, @Butter{2%TBSP}, salt and
pepper until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved sweet potato cooking
liquid as needed. Cover and set aside until ready to serve.

> Tip: If you like a sweeter mash, stir in a pinch of white sugar!

== Garlic-Sage Gravy ==

Melt @Butter{2%TBSP} in a medium pan over medium heat. Add garlic and half the
sage. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @Flour{1%tablespoon} and cook, whisking, until flour is lightly browned,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2} and @water{¾%cup}. Bring to a simmer and
cook, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Slice turkey crosswise.

Divide turkey, sweet potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Garnish
sweet potatoes with pecans. Drizzle turkey with as much gravy as you like and
garnish with remaining sage. Serve with any remaining gravy on the side.

> Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.